Document: RDShaderSPIRV
Path: godot/classes/class_rdshaderspirv.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of RDShaderSPIRV, including bytecode and compilation error messages for various shader stages.

Properties:
- `bytecode_any_hit` (PackedByteArray): The SPIR-V bytecode for the any hit shader stage. Default: PackedByteArray().
- `bytecode_closest_hit` (PackedByteArray): The SPIR-V bytecode for the closest hit shader stage. Default: PackedByteArray().
- `bytecode_compute` (PackedByteArray): The SPIR-V bytecode for the compute shader stage. Default: PackedByteArray().
- `bytecode_fragment` (PackedByteArray): The SPIR-V bytecode for the fragment shader stage. Default: PackedByteArray().
- `bytecode_intersection` (PackedByteArray): The SPIR-V bytecode for the intersection shader stage. Default: PackedByteArray().
- `bytecode_miss` (PackedByteArray): The SPIR-V bytecode for the miss shader stage. Default: PackedByteArray().
- `bytecode_raygen` (PackedByteArray): The SPIR-V bytecode for the ray generation shader stage. Default: PackedByteArray().
- `bytecode_tesselation_control` (PackedByteArray): The SPIR-V bytecode for the tessellation control shader stage. Default: PackedByteArray().
- `bytecode_tesselation_evaluation` (PackedByteArray): The SPIR-V bytecode for the tessellation evaluation shader stage. Default: PackedByteArray().
- `bytecode_vertex` (PackedByteArray): The SPIR-V bytecode for the vertex shader stage. Default: PackedByteArray().
Note: For all `bytecode_` properties, the returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedByteArray for more details.

Methods for `bytecode_` properties:
- Method: `set_stage_bytecode(stage: ShaderStage, bytecode: PackedByteArray)`
- Method: `get_stage_bytecode(stage: ShaderStage) -> PackedByteArray`

Properties:
- `compile_error_any_hit` (String): The compilation error message for the any hit shader stage (set by the SPIR-V compiler and Godot). If empty, shader compilation was successful. Default: "".
- `compile_error_closest_hit` (String): The compilation error message for the closest hit shader stage (set by the SPIR-V compiler and Godot). If empty, shader compilation was successful. Default: "".
- `compile_error_compute` (String): The compilation error message for the compute shader stage (set by the SPIR-V compiler and Godot). If empty, shader compilation was successful. Default: "".
- `compile_error_fragment` (String): The compilation error message for the fragment shader stage (set by the SPIR-V compiler and Godot). If empty, shader compilation was successful. Default: "".
- `compile_error_intersection` (String): The compilation error message for the intersection shader stage (set by the SPIR-V compiler and Godot). If empty, shader compilation was successful. Default: "".
- `compile_error_miss` (String): The compilation error message for the miss shader stage (set by the SPIR-V compiler and Godot). If empty, shader compilation was successful. Default: "".
- `compile_error_raygen` (String): The compilation error message for the ray generation shader stage (set by the SPIR-V compiler and Godot). If empty, shader compilation was successful. Default: "".
- `compile_error_tesselation_control` (String): The compilation error message for the tessellation control shader stage (set by the SPIR-V compiler and Godot). If empty, shader compilation was successful. Default: "".
- `compile_error_tesselation_evaluation` (String): The compilation error message for the tessellation evaluation shader stage (set by the SPIR-V compiler and Godot). If empty, shader compilation was successful. Default: "".
- `compile_error_vertex` (String): The compilation error message for the vertex shader stage (set by the SPIR-V compiler and Godot). If empty, shader compilation was successful. Default: "".

Methods for `compile_error_` properties:
- Method: `set_stage_compile_error(stage: ShaderStage, compile_error: String)`
- Method: `get_stage_compile_error(stage: ShaderStage) -> String`
